<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="244" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,153,755]" pageId="7" pageNumber="244">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,549,575]" pageId="7" pageNumber="244">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is similar in external appearance to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Stal)" authorityName="Stal" baseAuthorityName="Stal" box="[912,1174,548,575]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Drabescus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="244" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitens">
<emphasis box="[912,1105,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="244">Drabescus nitens</emphasis>
(Stål)
</taxonomicName>
(see below) and several new species from 
<collectingCountry box="[447,550,585,611]" name="Malaysia" pageId="7" pageNumber="244">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[608,717,585,611]" name="Indonesia" pageId="7" pageNumber="244">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
in the BMNH. All these species differ from typical 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1870" box="[1316,1436,585,611]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Drabescus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="244" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1316,1436,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="244">Drabescus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the fore margin of the head broadly rounded in profile (compare Figs 2B and 3B with 
<figureCitation box="[1242,1327,621,647]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1952,1977]" captionTargetBox="[194,1376,727,1920]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1398,701,1941]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Drabescus albofasciatus Cai &amp; He (male). A–B, habitus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively; C, head and thorax, dorsoanterior view; D. face; E. pygofer, lateral view; F–G, aedeagus, ventral and lateral view respectively; H, valve, subgenital plate and style, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3234332/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="244">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
) with the vertex relatively narrow and with the foremargin slightly angular near to each eye (Fig. 2C, 3C). The new species and those from 
<collectingCountry box="[326,429,693,719]" name="Malaysia" pageId="7" pageNumber="244">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[484,593,693,719]" name="Indonesia" pageId="7" pageNumber="244">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
also differ in having the foretibia distinctly flattened and expanded and the subgenital plates short (compare Fig. 
<date box="[573,596,729,755]" pageId="7" pageNumber="244">2I</date>
with 
<figureCitation box="[660,749,729,755]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1952,1977]" captionTargetBox="[194,1376,727,1920]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1398,701,1941]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Drabescus albofasciatus Cai &amp; He (male). A–B, habitus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively; C, head and thorax, dorsoanterior view; D. face; E. pygofer, lateral view; F–G, aedeagus, ventral and lateral view respectively; H, valve, subgenital plate and style, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3234332/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="244">Figs 1H</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[804,831,729,755]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1695,1720]" captionTargetBox="[229,1374,195,1674]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1398,187,1685]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Drabescus sp. A–F, D. nitens (Stål), female type; A–B, habitus, dorsal and lateral view respectively; C, head and thorax, dorsal view; D, face; E, forewing; F, abdominal terminalia, lateral view; G–N, Drabescus?nitens (Stål), male (Philippnes, BMNH); G, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; H, connective, ventral view; I, valve, ventral view; J, subgenital plate, ventral view; K, left style apex, lateral view; L, left style, ventral view; M–N, aedeagus lateral and ventral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3234334/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="244">3J</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
